sentence: Palestinians  continue  to  flee  from  northern  Gaza  ahead  of  an  expected  Israeli  strike  against  Hamas  targets  in  the  area,  one  week  after  Hamas  launched  a  multi-pronged  attack  inside  Israel,  killing  more  than  1,400  people.
Israeli  strikes  on  the  Gaza  Strip  have  killed  2,750  Palestinians,  with  9,700  wounded,  the  Gaza  Health  Ministry  announced.
Hamas  has  previously  claimed  that  13  hostages  have  been  killed  within  Gaza  by  Israeli  airstrikes.

Israel  has  launched  a  massive  response  to  the  deadly  attack  carried  out  on  Oct.  7  by  Hamas  militants  that  left  more  than  1,400  people  dead  in  Israel,  including  30  U.  S.  citizens.
The  Israeli  military  also  said  on  Sunday  that  at  least  286  of  its  soldiers  have  been  killed  in  the  past  week.
In  addition,  at  least  55  people  have  been  killed  in  the  West  Bank,  with  more  than  1,200  wounded,  the  Palestinian  Ministry  of  Foreign  Affairs  and  Expatriates  announced.
